"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-12-30-transfer-willians-olympiacos-contract-terminated\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Brazilian winger, Willian's contract with Olympiacos has been terminated.  This was disclosed by football transfer expert Fabrizio Romano in a tweet via his X account.  Willian had joined the Greek club this year after leaving Premier League side Fulham.  However, the 36-year-old is now available as a free agent ahead of the January transfer window.  \\\"Willian has just terminated his contract at Olympiacos, available as free agent,\\\" Romano tweeted on Monday.  \\\"Former Chelsea, Arsenal and Fulham winger will now be ready for new chapter.\\\"  This is not the first time Willian has terminated his contract in his career.  He terminated his contract with Arsenal to join Corinthians.  NPFL: Enyimba unveil former Super Eagles forward, Ideye  AFCONQ 2025: Nigeria cleared as CAF sanctions Libya, Benin Republic, Equatorial Guinea  Transfer: Club Brugge plot move for Fernandez  Transfer: Premier League clubs interested in Nigerian-born goalkeeper  Transfer: Rangers line up summer move for Sanusi  Transfer: Nwabali not concerned over free agent status  Transfer: Onazi moves to Lithuanian club FK Babrungas  Transfer: Barcelona eyes Chelsea's Pedro Neto as alternative to Marcus Rashford  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"